Kuwait Allows GCC Companies to Open Local Branches, KUNA Reports

-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 
2011-05-29T06:12:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-29/kuwait-allows-gcc-companies-to-open-local-branches-kuna-reports.html
Kuwait â€™s Ministry of Commerce and
Industry issued a decree allowing Gulf companies to open
branches in Kuwait, state-run  KUNA  reported, citing Commerce
Minister Amani Boresli.  The move is part of plans to boost economic integration
between members of the Gulf Cooperation Council states, Boresli
told KUNA. The decree excludes companies with foreign partners,
according to the minister.  The GCC comprises Kuwait,  Saudi Arabia , the  United Arab
Emirates , Oman, Qatar and Bahrain.  To contact the reporter on this story:
